properties.areaDesc: San Luis Obispo County Central Coast; Santa Barbara County Central Coast
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 31 at 2:12PM PST until February 2 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 25 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...San Luis Obispo and Santa Barbara County Central Coast.

* WHEN...From Sunday afternoon through Sunday evening.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down large objects such as
trees and power lines. Power outages are possible. Travel
could be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The strongest winds will be along the
immediate coast. Areas of blowing sand are likely near the
beaches resulting in reduced visibilities. Highways 1 and 101
will be affected.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH SUNDAY EVENING
